Roy F Weston Inc said it filed withthe Securitites and Exchange Commission a registrationstatement covering a 30 mln dlr issue of convertiblesubordinated debentures due 2002.    Plans for the proceeds include capital expenditures such asnew office buildings, equipment and facilities, the companysaid.  Weston also anticipates using the proceeds for possibleacquisitions of related businesses as well as for generalcorporate purposes.    Weston named Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc as sole manager ofthe offering. Reuter&#3;